1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bg5 c6 6. e3 Bf5 7. Qf3 Bg6 8. Bxf6 Qxf6 9. Qxf6 gxf6 { A well known position is reached -- White has damaged black's kingside pawn structure, but black has the bishop pair. The ensuing middlegame will be imbalanced with all three results possible. See Chapter 6 (Bologan-Short) for middlegame strategy } { [%cal Gb8d7,Gd7b6,Gf8e7,Ga7a5,Ga5a4] } *


