1. d4 d5 2. Nc3 { A lesser common but tricky opening where white aims to play an early e4 } 2... Nf6 3. Bg5 (3. e4 dxe4 4. f3 { The Blackmar-Diemer Gambit } 4... c6!? { A tricky response to decline the gambit } 5. fxe4 e5! 6. dxe5 Qxd1+ 7. Kxd1 Ng4 $15 { Black will win back the pawn with a comfortable position }) 3... Nbd7 { Reinforcing f6 and avoiding double pawns } (3... e6 4. e4 { Transposes to a mainline of the French-- usually what white is hoping for }) 4. f3 (4. e4 dxe4 5. f3 c6 { transposes to mainline }) 4... c6!? { Perhaps a suspicious looking move whose idea will become clear soon } 5. e4 dxe4 6. fxe4 e5! 7. dxe5 Qa5! $15 { A great resource! This is the reason black played c6 } { [%cal Ga5g5] } *


